
Overview of noun inflation

The noun inflation has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (1) inflation, rising prices -- (a general and progressive increase in prices; "in inflation everything gets more valuable except money")
2. inflation -- ((cosmology) a brief exponential expansion of the universe (faster than the speed of light) postulated to have occurred shortly after the big bang)
3. ostentation, ostentatiousness, pomposity, pompousness, pretentiousness, puffiness, splashiness, inflation -- (lack of elegance as a consequence of being pompous and puffed up with vanity)
4. inflation -- (the act of filling something with air)
